page.title: 12Ecology in Rogate
page.content: During our surveys we have found the following samples of flora and fauna. Red Campion, Buttercup, Wild Poppy, Cowparsley, Dogroses, Germander Speedwell, Dandelion, Comfrey, Knapweed, Rosebay Willowherb, Charlock, and Grannie pop out of bed. Frogs, slow worms, newts, an asortment of moths and butterflies and several stag beetles, both male and females. There was more evidence of squirrels, Roe deer, mice and rats both by the dung and the eating habits. Red Mice have a white flash on the chest they are one of the rarity of the area but we did not see any. However we estimated there were at least 6 field mice to a 10 metre square on one field test.
